<tt>Tue Nov 26  9:54:05 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
The Vietnam war was a &quot;tar baby&quot; conflict during the sixties and seventies.  No matter how hard we tried (as a nation and as individuals) to back out of that war, we just seemed to be pulled in deeper.  That war, unfortunately, is still a &quot;tar baby.&quot;  No matter how hard we try to move beyond it, it is always there.  We are either &quot;kicking the Vietnam syndrome,&quot; debating Bill Clinton's lack of participation (why doesn't Al Gore points for his participation?), or trying to bring about some sort of collective (or individual) closure.  Are we ever going to get beyond Vietnam in our lifetimes?
